## Built

### Markdown Hierarchy (2026-03-28)
- Node labels styled by `#` prefix: `# ` = H1, `## ` = H2, `### ` = H3
- Font size and weight vary by heading level
- `#` prefix stripped from display label
- Text wrapping via `wrapText()` helper using `<tspan>` elements â€” wrap length configurable via settings
- Question nodes: if `node.text` ends with `?`, node dot and label render in `questionColor`

### Settings Panel (2026-03-28)
- Gear icon (top-right) opens settings panel
- Settings persisted to `localStorage` under key `jewel_settings`
- Configurable: H1/H2/H3/default font sizes, node color, edge color, question color, wrap length, Tab indent X/Y, Shift+Enter indent Y
- Each setting has a slider + typeable number input (stay in sync)
- Color settings have a color picker + typeable hex input
- Fixed 300px width, no horizontal scroll
- Reset to defaults button
- Spinner arrows hidden on number inputs via `globals.css`

### Session Colors (2026-03-29)
- Each browser session gets one color from a 6-color palette: `#e879f9`, `#34d399`, `#fb923c`, `#38bdf8`, `#f472b6`, `#a78bfa`
- Color index cycles via `jewel_session_color_index` in `localStorage` â€” each page load picks the next color
- `getSessionColor()` in `src/lib/sessionColor.ts`
- On node creation, both `color` and `edgeColor` set to session color, persisted to DB
- Canvas renders: node fill = `node.color ?? settings.nodeColor`; edge stroke = `edge.color ?? settings.edgeColor`
- Temp nodes/edges carry session color before DB write for consistent rendering

**Bugfix (2026-03-29):** Was storing index in sessionStorage â€” new tabs shared it so color never changed. Rewrote to use localStorage for index only, no color caching.

### Hover Timestamps (2026-03-29)
- `mouseover` on any node group appends `<text class="timestamp-label">` below the node dot at `y = NODE_R + 18`
- Format: `toLocaleString` with `{ month: 'short', day: 'numeric', hour: 'numeric', minute: '2-digit' }` â€” e.g. "Mar 28, 2:14 PM"
- Style: `font-size: 9px`, `fill: #666`, `opacity: 0.6`, centered
- `mouseleave` removes the element

### Session Color Editor (2026-03-30)
- New API: `GET /api/canvases/[id]/session-colors` â€” queries nodes grouped by local date using `DISTINCT ON (created_at::date)`, returns `{ sessions: [{ date, color }] }` sorted newest first, wrapped in `withRetry`
- New API: `PATCH /api/canvases/[id]/session-colors` â€” accepts `{ date: string, color: string }`, updates `nodes.color` + `edges.color` for nodes created in that UTC day range, returns `{ updated: number }`
- Settings panel Colors section: Node and Edge global color rows removed; session colors merged in â€” Question (?) color, then Today's `SessionColorRow`, then "Past sessions" dropdown (only shown if past sessions exist)
- `SessionColorRow`: color picker + hex input + confirm checkmark (enabled only when dirty) â€” confirm fires PATCH then calls `onSessionColorChange` callback to repaint canvas without reload
- `PastSessionsDropdown`: pill trigger with rotating chevron; opens `position: fixed` floating list anchored via `getBoundingClientRect()`; closes on outside click via document listener; max-height 240px scrollable
- `onSessionColorChange` in `page.tsx`: updates `sessionColorRef.current` when date is today (so new nodes immediately use the new color), then remaps nodes/edges using `new Date(n.createdAt).toLocaleDateString('en-CA') === date` for local-timezone correctness

### Local Timezone Fix (2026-03-30)
- All session date keys were using `toISOString().slice(0, 10)` (UTC), which caused the day to flip at ~7â€“8pm EST
- Fixed in `sessionColor.ts`, `page.tsx` (onSessionColorChange), and `SettingsPanel.tsx` to use `toLocaleDateString('en-CA')` (returns `YYYY-MM-DD` in local time)
- Yesterday calculation in `SettingsPanel.tsx` changed from `setUTCDate` to `setDate` to match local timezone

